If you are able to run any Cucumber scenario at all you probebly are using the wrong import for the `@BeforeAll` annotation. Right ones are `io.cucumber.java.BeforeAll` and `io.cucumber.java.AfterAll`.

https://github.com/cucumber/cucumber-jvm/tree/main/java#hooks

```java
package io.cucumber.example;

import io.cucumber.java.AfterAll;
import io.cucumber.java.BeforeAll;

public class StepDefinitions {

    @BeforeAll
    public static void beforeAll() {
        // Runs before all scenarios
    }

    @AfterAll
    public static void afterAll() {
        // Runs after all scenarios
    }
}
```

If you are not able run any tests at all, and you want to use only JUnit 5, and you do not want to use JUnit Vintage with Cucumber JUnit then you can use the [`cucumber-junit-platform-engine`][1].

