The `Bukkit.getPluginManager().getPlugin()` method will try to find the plugin which have for name &quot;BlockProt&quot; in your case.

It can return null if it don&#39;t find the plugin. But, how can you avoid it ?

1. Check if the plugin exist/is enabled. It&#39;s better when you have lot of plugin, and you are sure that your plugin don&#39;t run BEFORE enabling of other plugin (i.e. at startup)
```
PluginManager pm = Bukkit.getPluginManager();
if(pm.isPluginEnabled(&quot;BlockProt&quot;)) {
   pm.disablePlugin(pm.getPlugin(&quot;BlockProt&quot;));
}
```
2. Try to disable it, but stop if the plugin can&#39;t be found. It will more be like your actual code.
```
Plugin pl = Bukkit.getPluginManager().getPlugin(&quot;BlockProt&quot;);
if(pl != null) {
   Bukkit.getPluginManager().disablePlugin(pl);
}
```

Don&#39;t forget to put in `softdepend` the plugin name that you are managing (here &quot;BlockProt&quot;), and also be sure it&#39;s the good name and the plugin is well on your server.

